sub_title: Electrical Engineer Grid Connections at Emergya Wind Technologies B.V.
summary:
Currently, an MSc Electrical Power Engineering student at TU Delft, with a specialization in the field of Smart AC and DC grids. I am interested in applying Machine Learning and Data Science in Power Systems. 

My ambition is to contribute into the energy transition within the power sector. I am a self-driven individual and I am eager to constantly learn more for both my professional and my personal development.

projects:
[{'title': 'Dispatching ambulances in the Netherlands with Deep Reinforcement Learning', 'date': {'start': {'month': 9, 'day': None, 'year': 2021}, 'end': {'month': 11, 'day': None, 'year': 2021}}, 'description': '- Applied Reinforcement Learning (RL) for solving Vehicle Route Problem (Ambulance Dispatching)
- Learnt about the state, action, reward method and Neural Networks
- Developed an improved ambulance dispatch algorithm using deep double Q-learning
- Although it is a simplified version of the real problem, we managed to exceed the performance of the greedy algorithm', 'contributors': [{'type': 'standardizedContributor', 'first_name': 'Thomas', 'last_name': 'Georgiou', 'name': None, 'headline': 'Electrical Engineer Grid Connections at Emergya Wind Technologies B.V.'}]}, {'title': 'Electricity Market Simulation Game', 'date': {'start': {'month': 9, 'day': None, 'year': 2021}, 'end': {'month': 11, 'day': None, 'year': 2021}}, 'description': '- Bid in a simulation game of electricity and a CO2 market as a power company
- Learnt the differences of variable/fixed cost bidding strategies
- Followed specific investment strategies regarding building/dismantling power plants that in the end made us the most profitable fictitious company in our simulation world
- Discovered the CO2 market influence on investment decisions and some differences of the investement sin reality', 'contributors': [{'type': 'standardizedContributor', 'first_name': 'Thomas', 'last_name': 'Georgiou', 'name': None, 'headline': 'Electrical Engineer Grid Connections at Emergya Wind Technologies B.V.'}]}, {'title': 'Distribution grid congestion market', 'date': {'start': {'month': 2, 'day': None, 'year': 2021}, 'end': {'month': 4, 'day': None, 'year': 2021}}, 'description': '- Co-simulation of a distribution grid with flexible loads, distributed generation and a congestion market on MATLAB/Simulink
- Solved the congestion issue of a specific distribution network, using congestion market with aggregators
- Explored the advantages that flexibility provides, which is important aspect in the increase of RES based generation
- Learnt about energy markets, ancillary services and the platform GOPACS in the Netherlands', 'contributors': [{'type': 'standardizedContributor', 'first_name': 'Thomas', 'last_name': 'Georgiou', 'name': None, 'headline': 'Electrical Engineer Grid Connections at Emergya Wind Technologies B.V.'}]}, {'title': 'Applications of Optimal Power Flow in Distribution Systems', 'date': {'start': {'month': 12, 'day': None, 'year': 2019}, 'end': {'month': 7, 'day': None, 'year': 2020}}, 'description': '- Diploma Thesis project
- Formulated an appropriate Optimal Power Flow (OPF) model, using second-order conic programming relaxations with Yalmip toolbox
- Implemented the OPF model on active and reactive control problems of active distribution networks
- Researched about convex optimization and different ways of relaxation
- Learnt about the TSO/DSOs responsibilities, such as planning, balancing after the economic dispatch and the need for their coordination', 'contributors': [{'type': 'standardizedContributor', 'first_name': 'Thomas', 'last_name': 'Georgiou', 'name': None, 'headline': 'Electrical Engineer Grid Connections at Emergya Wind Technologies B.V.'}]}]
